ned. In so doing, he argues for the necessity of establishing a method of critical exchange between climate science, black studies, and the surrounding theoretical inquiries of humanism and posthumanism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aCapitalismxEnvironmental aspectsxHistory. 0aCapitalismxSocial aspectsxHistory. 0aClimatic changesxEconomic aspectsxHistory. 0aClimatic changesxSocial aspectsxHistory. 0aGeology, StratigraphicyAnthropocene. 0aSlave tradezGhanaxHistory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishz978311070476108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020z9783110704563oZDB-23-DSP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478012030zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478012030423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478012030/original  a978-3-11-069631-8  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070476-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DSPb2020